                <h4>What is the voting age population of Buffalo, West Virginia?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Buffalo, West Virginia, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 883.  The voting age population is 46.0% male and 54.0% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Buffalo, West Virginia residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 21.4% of
                        the residents of Buffalo are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Buffalo, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Buffalo are 99.2% White, 0.4% Other and 0.3% American Indian.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Buffalo, West Virginia residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Buffalo, 14.9% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 22.5%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    11.4% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Buffalo.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Buffalo, West Virginia residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 48.2% of
                    Buffalo residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Buffalo, West Virginia residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    93.0% of
                    Buffalo residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 10.4%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 4.2%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Buffalo, West Virginia residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Buffalo residents aged 5 and older, 0.0% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                0.0% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                0.0% speak an Indo-European language, and
                0.0% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Buffalo, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Buffalo is 16.4%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Buffalo, West Virginia residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Buffalo, 19.9% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                    <h4>What is the median income in Buffalo, West Virginia?</h4>
